                  <msItem>
                     <p> BURY ST. EDMUND. <persName>
                           <forename>Katherine</forename>, daughter of <persName>
                              <forename>Norman</forename> of <surname>St. Edmund</surname>
                           </persName>
                        </persName>, 
                  grants and confirms to <persName>
                           <forename>Peter</forename> de <surname>Nereford</surname>
                        </persName>
                  the whole of her messuage which was Norman's her brother, in the village of 
                  <placeName key="place_104540">St. Edmund</placeName>, as a free burgage, for two farthings to be annually paid to 
                  the sacrist, viz. that messuage which lies near the house of <persName>
                           <forename>Arnald</forename> the priest</persName> 
                  towards the north; for this donation the sard Peter gave her 12 marks of silver 
                  'in pleno porthmannemoth, and 'hostolagium' for herself and two servants in the said messuage
                  for the term of her life. 
                  (<origDate notBefore="1210" notAfter="1220" precision="low">c. 1210-20</origDate>.) 
                  </p>
